# .sql files are pinned to LF so their bytes are identical on every checkout.
# keta_db's migration checksum (see Migration.checksum in
# packages/keta_db/lib/src/migrate.dart) hashes a migration file's raw bytes,
# and verifyMigrations compares that hash against what was recorded when the
# migration was applied. Under core.autocrlf=true, a Windows checkout would
# otherwise rewrite LF to CRLF on checkout — a different byte sequence, hence a
# different FNV-1a hash — and a schema that is actually current would false-fail
# verify at boot. Pinning eol=lf here means every checkout, on every platform,
# sees the exact bytes CI hashed.
*.sql text eol=lf
